              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="beeches_oct"></a>Purley Beeches working party. Sat October 20th 10 - 1 
                </h3>
                <p>There I was thinking, last month, that it would take two work days to get all 25 kilo of mixed narcissus bulbs into the ground, when up turned these ultra-keen Beavers and their leaders and in just a little over an hour the box was empty. We can now look forward to more spring colour next year in the three areas that were planted. Well done everyone, particularly our young helpers, hope to have you join us again. Nothing for it then, but to stick to the original plan for this October work party and continue to clear paths of overhanging branches and undergrowth. Our new trees will also deserve some attention, although the nettles will start to die back soon the brambles do need continually keeping in check. If you have a hour or so free on the morning of the 20th do come and help, the usual team will be more than welcoming and as one of the Leaders of the Beavers said “That was so much fun”. It really is one of those times when work is actually fun.</p>
                <p>All the usual stuff. Signs from the Beech Avenue entrance will point the way. We meet at 10am and finish at the latest by 1pm. Please wear suitable protective clothing and gloves, think brambles, and any hand-tools, loppers, bow-saws, rakes etc. and don’t forget to bring your favourite beverage and snack for a late elevenses.</p>
                 <p><%= link_to "Friends of Purley Beeches work programme for 2018", "/resource/fopb2018.pdf" %></p>
                <p>For further information please email or call
                <ul><li>Stanley Lowy: 020 8657 3684 or stanlowy@outlook.com</li>
                <li>Elizabeth Bennett: bennett_e@sky.com</li>
                <li>Mac Court   mac@skyy.me.uk</li></ul></p>
              </td>
